      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i was looking into something and honestly it's kinda creeping me out. do u think it's actually possible for companies like google or amazon to use \"affective computing\" to basically read how people are feeling through their smart home devices? like if the lights or the thermostat change right when im feeling stressed or something... is that a real thing they could be doing to monitor people?",
